# Y · environment variables
#
# Copy to .env (or .env.local) and fill in. The defaults below cover the
# 100% local edge demo; cloud values are only needed for the "Cloud (Gemma 4
# 31B)" toolbar option.

# --- Edge (Ollama) -----------------------------------------------------------

# Where the Ollama daemon is reachable.
OLLAMA_HOST=http://localhost:11434

# Default Ollama tag for the "Edge (E4B)" tutor.
MODEL_NAME=gemma4:e4b

# Ollama tag for the "Edge fine-tuned" tutor. Created by:
#   ollama create y-gemma4 -f models/Modelfile.y-gemma4
# (See models/README.md.) If your tag is different, override here.
MODEL_NAME_EDGE_FT=y-gemma4

# Ollama embedding model used by the learner module. Pre-pull once via:
#   ollama pull nomic-embed-text
EMBED_MODEL=nomic-embed-text

# Learner adapter execution device. Omit to auto-select CUDA when available.
# ADAPTER_DEVICE=cuda
# Optional global checkpoint; the built-in default is models/learner-adapter-v1.safetensors.
# LEARNER_ADAPTER_CHECKPOINT=models/learner-adapter-v1.safetensors

# --- OpenAI Build Week teacher ---------------------------------------------

# GPT-5.6 is selected by default in the UI whenever this key is present.
# The whiteboard PNG is sent to OpenAI only while this cloud mode is selected.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-5.6-sol
OPENAI_EVIDENCE_MODEL=gpt-5.6-terra

# Salt used before a learner id is sent as OpenAI safety_identifier.
# Set a private random value in production; raw learner ids are never sent.
# SAFETY_ID_SALT=replace-with-a-private-random-value

# --- Local Kokoro speech ----------------------------------------------------

# Install once with: cd api && uv sync --extra speech
# Set to 1 to download Heart/Michael assets at startup instead of first use.
SPEECH_PREFETCH=0
# After running api/scripts/prefetch_speech.py, require exact asset hashes.
SPEECH_REQUIRE_LOCK=0
# MOONSHINE_VOICE_CACHE=data/tts-assets
# SPEECH_CACHE_DIR=data/speech-cache

# --- Cloud (Google AI Studio · Gemma 4 31B) ---------------------------------

# Install the optional cloud dep first:
#   cd api && uv pip install -e .[cloud]
#
# Get a key from https://aistudio.google.com/. Required ONLY for the cloud
# toolbar option; left blank, /lesson with model_choice=cloud will return a
# polite "API key not set" error and the demo continues with edge models.
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=

# Cloud model identifier passed to the GenAI SDK. Use the bare id
# `gemma-4-31b-it` on google-genai >=2.1; on 2.0.x you may need
# `models/gemma-4-31b-it`. Other valid ids: gemma-4-4b-it, gemma-4-e4b-it.
CLOUD_MODEL=gemma-4-31b-it

# --- Frontend ---------------------------------------------------------------

# Where the API is reachable from the browser. Override on Vercel deploys.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE=http://localhost:8000

# Optional comma-separated browser origins allowed by the API in addition to
# localhost and *.vercel.app. Use this if you deploy the frontend on a custom
# domain.
# CORS_ORIGINS=https://your-domain.com
